subSubSection.paragraph:
Description. (
Holotype
). Head naked. Lateral cephalic rounded. Antenna 1, first peduncular article with plumose setae in dorsal and ventral margins; article 2, 0.3 × article 1 length, with plumose and simple setae in anterodorsal and anteroventral corners; primary flagellum with 10 articles, two fields of callynophore, one strong and another weak, articles with simple setae in corners; accessory flagellum with six articles. Antenna 2, articles 4 and 5 subrectangular, approximately the same length, with simple and plumose setae; peduncle 7-articulate.
